
pantherScore2.0.pl - a script to score protein sequences against the
hmmer3 PANTHER HMM library using  hmmer3 programs


Usage:
    pantherScore2.0.pl -l <PANTHER library> -D B -V 
                    -i <fasta file> -o <output file>

Example:


use hmmscan:
./pantherScore2.0.pl -l PANTHER11.1 -D B -V -H ./hmmer-3.1b2/binaries/ -i homo_sapiens.fasta -o homo_sapiens.out -n

use hmmsearch:
./pantherScore2.0.pl -l PANTHER11.1 -D B -V -H ./hmmer-3.1b2/binaries/ -i homo_sapiens.fasta -o homo_sapiens.out -n -s

Where args are:
	-h for help (this message)
	-l PANTER (l)ibrary with HMMs when using hmmsearch, binary PANTHER HMM model when using hmmscan
	-D display type for results
		options: I (interproscan), B (best hit), A (all hits)
	-E user defined hmm (E)value cutoff to over ride default
	-s to use hmmsearch instead of hmmscan for scoring sequence againt hmm library 
	-H user defined path to direcgtory contating hmmer3 binary executables (including hmmscan or hmmsearch)
		default: hmmer3 binary in $PATH
	-z user defined path to gun(z)ip path
		default: gunzip binary in $PATH
	-n to display family and subfamily names in the output
	-T user defined path for tmp directory
		default: /tmp/
	-o (o)utput file (redirect STDOUT)
	-i (i)nput fasta file to score
	-t for entry (t)ype
	-n to display family and subfamily names in the output
	-P P=1 to for (P)roduction format of lib; P=0 for build version
		default: 1
	-c for number of (c)pu on machine to use for blast/hmmsearch
		default: 1
	-e (e)rror file (redirect STDERR)
	-v (v)erbose (debug info to STDERR)
	-V (V)ery verbose (debug info to STDERR)
Error: Cannot find library ../../data/PANTHER11.1.


